Ticket Description: Probe MSI installer failed with 'LicenseAccepted' error during setup.
Resolution: Added `/QN` and `LicenseAccepted=yes` to the MSI command; reinstalled successfully.

Ticket Description: Subnet didn’t populate automatically after converting asset to probe.
Resolution: Manually added subnet under Network Monitor > Network Scans.

Ticket Description: SNMP credential test failed with timeout errors.
Resolution: Updated SNMP port from 162 to 161 and verified read community string.

Ticket Description: Added probe doesn’t appear in probe list for selected client.
Resolution: Probe was installed under wrong site; corrected client mapping.

Ticket Description: User unable to trigger scan for subnet.
Resolution: Added active probe to subnet; scan option re-enabled.

Ticket Description: Error 'Subnet already exists' displayed while adding subnet.
Resolution: Verified existing subnet entry and updated CIDR range.

Ticket Description: User unable to delete credential linked to active probe.
Resolution: Removed probe dependency first, then deleted credential.

Ticket Description: Error: 'OID configuration already exists.'
Resolution: Renamed duplicate OID entry; saved successfully.

Ticket Description: Router showing 70% packet loss in ICMP monitor.
Resolution: Checked latency, rebooted router; packet loss reduced to 0%.

Ticket Description: SSH terminal not opening from SuperOps.
Resolution: Added correct SSH credential; confirmed remote shell access.

Ticket Description: Probe couldn’t fetch SNMPv3-enabled asset details.
Resolution: Updated authentication method from MD5 to SHA; re-scan successful.

Ticket Description: ICMP response time graph not rendering.
Resolution: Cleared cache and restarted agent; graphs reloaded.

Ticket Description: Discovered asset listed as 'unknown' though it’s a Cisco switch.
Resolution: Added manufacturer and device type manually; now listed as known asset.

Ticket Description: Custom monitor alert condition not creating ticket.
Resolution: Enabled alert toggle in policy configuration; ticket triggers verified.

Ticket Description: Network scan taking longer than expected.
Resolution: Reduced SNMP timeout from 10s to 5s; improved scan time.

Ticket Description: User unable to turn off SNMP on printer asset.
Resolution: Enabled Configure option under asset settings; disabled SNMP successfully.

Ticket Description: Error while linking credential to site.
Resolution: Recreated deleted credential; linked successfully.

Ticket Description: Probe uninstall command not removing agent.
Resolution: Stopped service manually; re-ran uninstall with elevated privileges.

Ticket Description: WMI scan failed on endpoint with 'Access Denied.'
Resolution: Corrected domain\username format and restarted WinRM service.

Ticket Description: Ping showing high latency (350ms).
Resolution: Checked bandwidth utilization; optimized routing; latency stable at 50ms.

Ticket Description: Probe status inactive post installation.
Resolution: Opened firewall port 443 for outbound connection; probe online.

Ticket Description: Network scan completed but no assets listed.
Resolution: Probe not linked to subnet; re-mapped and re-ran scan.

Ticket Description: Multiple duplicate alerts generated for same switch issue.
Resolution: Increased cool-off period in policy to 30 minutes.

Ticket Description: Printer-specific policy not available under settings.
Resolution: Enabled printer policy view from Settings > Policy Management.

Ticket Description: Device reachable via SNMP but showing ICMP only.
Resolution: Updated SNMP credentials and rescanned asset.

Ticket Description: Custom monitor graph not plotting data.
Resolution: Enabled 'time-series' option during monitor setup; graph visible.

Ticket Description: Custom monitor expression throwing error.
Resolution: Fixed dependent monitor reference; validated successfully.

Ticket Description: Network scan shows 'no probe found' error.
Resolution: Added active probe for that subnet and re-initiated scan.

Ticket Description: Error while converting existing asset into probe.
Resolution: Asset missing SNMP credentials; added new credential and retried.

Ticket Description: Device marked offline though reachable manually.
Resolution: Restarted SNMP service; asset showing online.

Ticket Description: SNMP OID returns empty value for switch metric.
Resolution: Verified OID against manufacturer MIB; replaced correct OID.

Ticket Description: Probe can’t discover endpoints using WMI.
Resolution: Started WinRM service on probe and endpoint.

Ticket Description: SSH Terminal button missing in UI.
Resolution: Upgraded to latest agent version; SSH terminal enabled.

Ticket Description: Alerts not closing automatically post fix.
Resolution: Checked Reset checkbox in policy; verified auto-close working.

Ticket Description: Default printer monitors not showing under asset class.
Resolution: Re-enabled default monitors in Settings > Asset class > Printer.

Ticket Description: Probe using 90% CPU during large subnet scan.
Resolution: Limited concurrent SNMP requests and reduced scan interval.

Ticket Description: User unable to edit saved network policy.
Resolution: Changed policy ownership permissions; edit allowed.

Ticket Description: No alerts despite 50% packet loss.
Resolution: Configured alert for 'Packet Loss > 30% for 10 mins'; tested OK.

Ticket Description: Device marked failed after scan retries.
Resolution: Increased SNMP retry count from 1 to 3; asset discovered.

Ticket Summary: NAS not listed under network devices
Ticket Description: NAS device discovered but not categorized correctly.
Resolution: Added NAS type manually; monitored via SNMP.

Ticket Description: Installation log not generated post install.
Resolution: Added `/L*V 'installation.log'` flag in MSI command.

Ticket Description: Alert generated after long delay.
Resolution: Reduced polling interval from 30m to 5m for faster detection.

Ticket Description: Duplicate entries for same device.
Resolution: Cleared duplicate SNMP responses; deduped via IP.

Ticket Description: Probe showing 'no credential assigned.'
Resolution: Linked correct SNMP credential in probe settings.

Ticket Description: Interface throughput metrics not updating.
Resolution: Refreshed custom OID; verified real-time update.

Ticket Description: SSH authentication failed with wrong key.
Resolution: Re-uploaded correct key; SSH terminal accessible.

Ticket Description: Devices missing after discovery scan.
Resolution: Verified WMI/SSH credentials and restarted scan.

Ticket Description: Community string reset post restart.
Resolution: Updated stored credential and locked configuration.

Ticket Description: Policy trigger didn’t send notification.
Resolution: Added email action to policy; verified mail delivery.

Ticket Description: User unable to monitor network devices.
Resolution: Activated Network Monitoring add-on under license settings.
